before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"3cgdt","text":"Buffer Recipe: (65.7 ml of DDH2O + 1ml of 0.204 M CaCl2 + 33.3ml of 0.3M sodium cacodylate pH 7.4)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":98}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"969en","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"11cad","text":"Fixative in conical tube: 2.0 ml from 25% EM grade glutaraldehyde stock vial, 1.0 ml of 0.3M stock sodium cacodylate buffer and 22.0 ml of 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"60qa9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
description: {"blocks":[{"key":"boqf2","text":"This protocol uses APEX2, an engineered peroxidase that genetically targets a cellular region of interest, to oxidatively polymerize Ln-DAB2, (lanthanum chelates conjugated to DAB), using hydrogen peroxide. We use these precipitated lanthanum metals to identify the labeled regions of interest by using EELS and elemental mapping.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

funders.funder_name: UCSD Graduate Training Programs in Cellular and Molecular Pharmacology

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6crkd","text":"HEK293T cells are cultured on imaging plates containing poly-d-lysine coated glass bottom No. 0 coverslips (P35GC-0-14C, MatTek Corporation).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bfhkn","text":"Cells are transiently transfected with either APEX2-H2B or mitochondrial matrix-APEX2 fusion using Lipofectamine 3000 (Life Technologies). APEX2 is fused to N-terminal of H2B and to C- terminal of mito matrix.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a7cfd","text":"After 16 hours transfection, cells are fixed with 2% EM grade glutaraldehyde (18426, Ted Pella Incorporated) in 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4 (18851, Ted Pella Incorporated) containing 2 mM CaCl2 for 5 minutes at 37°C and then on ice for 55 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":202,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1tbdc","text":"Fixative is removed and cells are rinsed with 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4 (5X1min) on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"98p3u","text":"On a set plates, an enzymatic reaction with Ln-DAB2 with 4 mM H2O2 (from 30%) in 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer at pH 7.4 until the desired brown intensity color from the precipitate, between 2 to 30 minutes. (1ul of 9.8M H2O2 added in 2500 ul or 2.5 ml Ln-DAB2 solution). See making of Ln-DAB2 solutions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":50,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":63,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":65,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":222,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":224,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":259,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":292,"length":1},{"style":"bold","offset":272,"length":32}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5u9pg","text":" After reactions, all plates of cells are rinsed with 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4 containing 2 mM CaCl2 (5X1min) on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":112,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c5g8v","text":"Cells are post-fixed with either 0.01% ruthenium tetroxide (20700-05, Electron Microscopy Sciences) or 1% reduced  osmium tetroxide (19150, Electron Microscopy Sciences) containing 2 mM CaCl2  and 0.8% potassium ferrocyanide in 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4 for 30 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":190,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"el5rh","text":"Post fixative is removed from cells and are rinsed with 0.1M sodium cacodylate buffer at pH 7.4 (5X1min) on ice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3t9f0","text":" An ice-cold graded dehydration ethanol series of 20%, 50%, 70%, 90%, 100% (anhydrous) for one minute each and 2X 100% (anhydrous) at room temperature for 1 minute each.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6f88c","text":"Add 20mM glycine in 0.10M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4 for 15-20 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9itpg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6iiqv","text":"Rinse cells 2x for 1 minute with the 0.10M sodium cacodylate buffer, pH 7.4. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e1611","text":"Cells were infiltrated with one part Durcupan ACM epoxy resin (44610, Sigma-Aldrich) to one part anhydrous ethanol for 30 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8p2o8","text":"Plates are changed three times with 100% Durcupan resin for 1 hours each with the first change having the lid only partly covering the top of the plate, a final change of Durcupan resin and immediately placing the plate without the lid in a vacuum oven at 60°C for 48 hours to harden.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bdqcv","text":"After 15 minutes, the 0.01% ruthenium tetroxide solution should be removed and replaced with new 0.01% ruthenium tetroxide solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
